\b0 Andy Thompson (andrewt@caltech.edu)\
Last updated:  July 17, 2020
\b \
\

\b0 The mixed layer data product \'93MLD_all.mat\'94 provides calculations of mixed layer depth for key platforms during the EXPORTS 2018 North Pacific field program.  The default criterion for mixed layer depth is the depth at which the density difference, compared to the density at 5 m, exceeds 0.1 kg/m^3.  This choice was selected in order to pick out the strong thermocline at the mixed layer base, as opposed to shorter term stratification events due to surface forcing.  Please contact Andy Thompson (andrewt@caltech.edu) if you have interest in other MLD criteria.\
